@mdeuser I think looks OK.
I like to see that we auto detect extension file.

You think we don't need also a flag `--format yaml`? on create `wsk api create --config-file myapi.yaml --format yaml`

Also following is the error noted
wsk -i activation result 23d80bf91ec7458183b419a73d5a3e76
{
    "error": "The action exceeded its time limits of 60000 milliseconds."
}

@mrutkows I exactly used `ansible-playbook -i environments/distributed provision_env_dist.yml` but after that I ended up removing `hosts.j2` file and hardcoding server ip's in `environments/distributed/hosts` file. But the next steps were also failure.

Docker-compose deployment seemed promising, and I thought we could scale it up easily using Docker Swarm but I think Docker-Compose needs some updates. It is for example using `links` directive and as it seems that containers can't see each other (my conclusion was that controller container can't see consul) because of that.

I'll work on it a bit more and post updates.

@cagataygurturk , which error did you get after setting up your hosts file? Were you able to successfully run the `ansible all -i environments/distributed -m ping` command? 

Also, I'm not too sure about that `inventory_ignore_extensions = templates` parameter, we want to just skip that single broken template file, not all of them. So you might want to remove that line from `ansible.cfg` since you've already removed the bad template file. You can also reach out to me on the Openwhisk slack channel if you'd like, my handle there is kkbankol 

@rabbah , whenever you get a chance, can you remove that bad template file at `ansible/environments/distributed/templates/hosts.j2`
